  {"f":"test_ollama.py","s":"This Python script tests the Ollama language model to summarize text. It initializes a model, constructs a prompt, sends the prompt to the Ollama API, captures the response, measures the response time, and prints the response and time taken.  The script handles potential errors during the API call and prints error messages if any occur.","c":["chat","JSON","Ollama API","time","ollama"],"m":["Ollama","response","text","prompt","model","time taken","test","error","summarize"],"i":[],"ub":[]},
  {"f":"THEORY.md","s":"Optimo-Algo is a system designed to drastically reduce API costs and context window usage for high-tier AI coding agents like GPT-4 and Claude 3.5 Sonnet by leveraging a local LLM (Ollama) to pre-process a codebase and generate a `TOON` representation.","c":["TOON (Token Oriented Object Notation)","The Optimo-Algo Workflow","Local Engine (Ollama)"],"m":["c: Class","m: Method/Function","d: Directory","s: Summary","f: File"],"i":[],"ub":[]},
