  {"f":"src\\config.py","s":"This code module defines configuration management for an AI model named Gemma3. It loads configuration settings from a JSON file, allowing for per-project customization. The `get_config_path()` function determines the location of the configuration file. The `load_config()` function reads the configuration from the file, merges it with a default configuration, and returns the modified configuration. The `save_config()` function writes the configuration to a file.  The `set_model()` function sets the model name, while `add_ignore()` adds ignore rules.  `get_model()` retrieves the model name from the configuration. `get_extra_ignores()` retrieves the extra ignore rules from the configuration. The code utilizes a JSON file for configuration storage and retrieval, ensuring a structured approach to managing model settings and ignore rules.","c":["save_config","get_extra_ignores","add_ignore","config.py","load_config","get_model"],"m":["save_config","get_extra_ignores","add_ignore","config.py","load_config","get_model"],"i":[],"ub":[]},
